robust defence by the parents and wider community.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2) Community makeup</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">: currently 86 adults; 21 under-18s</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3) Housing availability and ownership</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">31 permanently-occupied owner-occupied dwellings (including 3 caravans)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">18 permanently-occupied leased dwellings (including 1 caravan)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">30 holiday homes</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">8 empty houses</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3 derelict houses</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4) Land ownership:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3 estates (of which an approx. total area of 20,000 acres lies within community boundary)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2 farms (approx. 1,000 acres each)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2 very small holdings (less than 20 acres)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">5 crofts (4 owner-occupied)</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5) House and building plot prices</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">one plot currently on sale for offers over £150,000</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">one house currently on sale for offers over £290,000</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">8 building plots sold in last 10 years (resulting in 7 holiday homes and 1 permanent home)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3 houses sold in last 10 years (all now holiday homes)</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">6) Local lease arrangements</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">: several houses (and one business) are let on 1988 Short Assured Tenancies, which default to month to month tenure (with two months notice to quit) after the initial 6 months term, giving no security to households or the affected business in an area where there are effectively no alternative homes or premises available.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">It is my opinion that month-to-month tenancy arrangements can cause tenants a high level of insecurity and stress, especially in an area with no or very little alternative accommodation.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">7) The </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Ulva</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> Ferry Community Development Plan</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A Community Development Plan has been created by the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Ulva</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Ferry Local Development Officers (part of the Growth at the Edge project), via a process of community consultation. I have identified the following areas of our Community Development Plan which I believe are directly affected by issues relating to land reform:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">A)</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Affordable Housing</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> –</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">as can be seen from the figures in 6) above, house prices and building plot prices are extremely high and unaffordable to those on average local wages</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">plots rarely become available and the majority are bought for second homes</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">most landowners are simply not interested in selling plots for affordable housing</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">there is only one socially-rented house in the area</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ten other houses are available to rent from private landlords, some at prohibitively high rates</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">some houses are let in sub-standard condition and are expensive to heat and keep aired</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">initially-promising efforts to collaborate with a local estate to create an affordable housing development unfortunately foundered due to financial circumstances </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">outwith</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the estate's control</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">a small landowner is currently working with the community to try to develop a similar affordable housing project but is constrained by personal economics</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">It is my opinion that having even a little community-owned land could allow development of affordable housing, complete with a housing chain to allow all ages to live in the community. This housing chain is severely lacking at this time in our area.  This would avoid the complexities involved with working with third-party landowners, who may have their own set of issues and constraints.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">The acquisition of land could be encouraged by tax breaks for sale or gifts of land to communities.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Housing and land burdens placed on such homes or land would ensure continued affordability in perpetuity and prevent profiteering.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">In our opinion the Woodland Croft model as pioneered by the North West Mull Community Woodland Company is a good working model of community land ownership, allowing young people to build starter homes and remain within their home community.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">B)</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">"Tenant / Landlord relations"</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> –</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">some community residents have felt afraid to raise tenancy issues, particularly relating to condition and maintenance of property</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">some tenants are unaware of their legal rights regarding standards of building maintenance</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">in this area, most communication between housing and business tenants and their landowner/landlord is indirect, via a factor based </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">outwith</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the community sometimes landlords decisions are made at infrequent or prolonged intervals due to the structure of the landlord's management / decision-making process which can lead to delays in decisions relating to tenants' businesses</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">some tenants live in fear that their domestic or business tenancies will be ended with only two months' notice in an area where there is effectively no alternative housing or business premises to relocate to</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">It is my opinion that community factoring may provide a more direct, rapid, accessible and 'comfortable' means for tenants to explore issues they may be experiencing.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">There should be clear, readily-accessible information for tenants regarding their tenants' rights.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">It is my opinion that month-to-month tenancy arrangements can cause tenants a high level of insecurity and stress, especially in an area with no or very little alternative accommodation.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">C)</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Economic development</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> –</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the Community Development Plan has highlighted the need for economic development, and identified most appropriate potential developments / improvements to be based around the existing harbour / waterfront area, where a deteriorating pier is threatening local fishermen’s and tour operators' livelihoods</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">it is hoped that the owner of the pier will continue recent signs of positive engagement with the local fishermen's group to revitalise the crumbling structure, as it is essential for the livelihoods of the area's fishermen</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">a small landowner has shown willing to explore a pontoon development to assist local tour operators and allow visiting yachts to berth - should the pier continue to deteriorate this may be the only means for the fishermen to land their catch</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">It is my opinion that there should be clear requirements / incentives for upkeep of vital community infrastructure, e.g. a law specifically to identify and protect core assets essential for survival of the economy of a community. There should be a body to advocate for communities should there be no amicable means of engagement and only as a last resort should there be need for measures such as additional taxation or compulsory purchase.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Community ownership of land and core community assets would allow community self-determination and security and encourage economic development.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">D)</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Energy</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> –</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">energy self-sufficiency was seen as important for our area, whether by means of a renewable community electricity project or multiple household installations</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">local landowners may be considering joint ventures or facilitating a community-led project</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">It is my opinion that having even a little community-owned land could allow greater potential for community-based energy projects without the need to involve private landowners.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">RECOMMENDATIONS FOR ACTION</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">1)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Increased support for community land ownership and self-governance as this provides opportunities and resilience in the following areas</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Housing (affordability / progression via housing chain / security of tenure / security for access to loans / crofts)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Employment (social and individual enterprise / business premises / land-based businesses e.g. crofts)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Food security (gardening / allotments / </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">crofting</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> / smallholdings / farms)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Energy security (community </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">renewables</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Avoidance of complexities associated with dealing with private landowners</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">2)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Tax breaks for the sale or gift of land or assets to communities to encourage philanthropy</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">3)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Independent assessment process to identify - and clear requirement in law to upkeep - vital community infrastructure / core assets, with recourse to additional taxation or compulsory purchase as a last resort should this fail to happen</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Advocacy / mediation service for communities in need where engagement with landowners or core asset-holders has failed</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">5)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Abolition of month-to-month style tenancy arrangements in favour of longer tenures, particularly in rural areas</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">6)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Support for community factoring</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">7)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Community accountability of land ownership via external auditing / independent appraisal of level of benefit of land and asset management to the local community, with subsequent  recourse to advocacy / action in case of poor or negative results. Examples of factors assessed could be: housing; agricultural use; sporting use; supporting and sustaining the local community. Examples of actions which could be taken could be: increased taxation or compulsory purchase</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">8)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Increased support for educational initiatives e.g. Forest Schools and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Crofting</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Connections which expand young people’s sense of relationship to land and community</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">9)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Increased access to information on land reform for communities and school children to increase awareness of the opportunities (and in some cases pitfalls) associated with community land ownership, plus support for inter-community networking and mentoring</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">10)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">New company structures or legal states to allow a community group to function </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">outwith</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the "Company Limited By Guarantee" vehicle could strengthen the culture of community land / asset management  groups. These could, for example, also function as SCIOs / Community Interest Groups or Scottish Charities</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">11)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Land value taxation</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">COMMENTS SPECIFICALLY RELATING TO THE COMMITTEE'S TERMS OF REFERENCE:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">These are the questions I feel relate best to my community. Most of the answers cross-refer to previous comments.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Q. Is the current land ownership pattern contributing to, or inhibiting, economic and community development?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A. Economic and community development in rural areas is highly-dependent on access to land for housing and business use. If land owners, large or small, are unwilling for whatever reason/s to release land for community development there is little prospect of that community developing. Some landowners are extremely pro-active and supportive of their local communities whilst it appears that others have no interest.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Q. How easy is it for communities in Scotland to take ownership of land and other assets? Should it be made easier in the light of the substantial achievements of existing community ownership groups?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A. “</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Crofting</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> communities” have an absolute right-to-buy. Other non-</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">crofting</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> communities can register an interest in pre-emptive right-to-buy but in reality there is often little chance of land coming onto the market. Even a little land could in some cases make an enormous difference to the future of communities and in light of the successes of existing community ownership groups, any means of increasing the chances of obtaining even a small amount of land should be considered positively, e.g. providing tax breaks for landowners who sell or gift land to communities. Clearly, positive, mutual engagement between communities and landowners should be sought and explored, but where this fails, even after intervention of a suggested independent “Advocacy / Mediation” body - and if there is independent assessment that this land is necessary for the community's survival - a means of compulsory purchase could be used. This applies equally to core infrastructure e.g. piers, airstrips and accesses. It is conceivable that some landowners who may be struggling to maintain their land and associated infrastructure may even welcome the opportunity to receive tax breaks in return for releasing land and other assets to communities to either manage or own.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Q. Is there a case for establishing a Land Agency to facilitate both the expansion of community ownership and the creation of new, especially "starter" tenancies, on land acquired for this purpose?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A. Yes, this could be extremely helpful. Most community groups are made up of hard-pressed volunteers who may struggle to find the resources of manpower, time and money required to pursue obtaining land for community use. “Starter” tenancies could bring in a new generation of younger people and families to rural communities, strengthening and enhancing those communities. In this area, for example, even one new family could make a big difference to the community and the school.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Q. How easy is it for land in public ownership to be transferred to communities and other private individuals, where that would be in the public interest? Should steps be taken to make it easier?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A. We are uncertain of how easy it is but it certainly should be facilitated as far as possible.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Q. Should a Land Value Tax of some sort be introduced in Scotland, as a replacement or addition to council tax and business rates?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A. Revenue from Land Value Tax raised in addition to council tax and business rates could be ring-fenced to fund community development projects and other common good projects within the area of origin.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">There is a very big need for land reform especially in areas that are fragile with regards to a sustainable population. I hope that the points raised are taken into account.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p></div></body></html>